name: Tenryuu Kai Ni
description:
This is my first attempt at making a Lora and I see someone already uploaded one for Tenryuu today. Honestly the one made by Foxtrott gives much better results overall.
Still uploading this as it does look to have a different style and it can generate usable images. Best to use weights between 0.6 and 0.8
Best for making Tenryuu Kai Ni but it can also create her base version, see example pics for fitting prompts.

Updated my dataset a bit but I'm pretty sure I'm doing something wrong somewhere in the whole process...
Trained for 4Epochs and it's a bit overbaked so weights should be lowered to 0.6-0.7

If anyone has any recommended settings for the training let me know!

modelVersions.name: 2E2
modelVersions.description: Should probably have uploaded this a lot sooner, just another training with a few different settings and I tend to use these most often. Can be hit or miss with details and especially the eyepatch. I've included examples with a few different models to give a general idea. If you're interested in my Tenryuu Lora I'd suggest getting them all and just trying which one works best for you.
